Login System with Role‑Based Administration
This project is a secure login system built using Python, SQLite, and Tkinter.
It supports user registration, authentication, password recovery, and administrative account management through a graphical interface.

Security Features

Passwords are hashed using SHA‑256 before storage
Plaintext passwords are never saved or displayed
Role‑based access control separates users from administrators

Database Design

SQLite is used for lightweight local storage
User data includes usernames, hashed passwords, recovery questions, and account roles
The database automatically initializes and upgrades when required

User Capabilities

Sign up for an account
Log in securely
Recover forgotten passwords using security questions

Administrator Capabilities

View registered user accounts (read‑only)
Promote users to administrator roles
Reset user passwords safely
Access is controlled via database‑stored roles, not hard‑coded rules

Graphical Interface

Tkinter is used solely as a presentation layer
Core authentication and security logic remains unchanged
The GUI improves usability without compromising security

Design Philosophy
The system follows a clean separation of concerns:

Logic layer: authentication, hashing, database rules
UI layer: input and display using Tkinter

This design ensures maintainability, scalability, and strong security practices.
